engine

Class Sai

  • java.lang.Object
    • engine.Sai

  • public class Sai
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to hold the Selection, Action, Input, (i.e. SAI) that a rule suggests when that rule fires. Please note: Selection indicates which interface element/working memory element should be updated Action indicates how the interface element should be updated. (if its a table it can be "Update Table", if it is a dropdown element it can be "UpdateDropDown". Input indicates what value should that interface element / working memory element should take.
    Author:
    Nikolaos Barmpalios {nbarmpalios@gmail.com}
